    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level of 3 due to single-condition testing; this gap is accepted given Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence, and the conservative nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol. All three primary QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for the stated COU. Note: aleatory variability in the force-at-40mm QoI was characterized qualitatively rather than through a formal structured UQ analysis; this represents a documentation gap that does not affect the overall acceptance decision given the conservative E/uval margin for that QoI.",
